<link href="~/Content/Site.css" rel="stylesheet" />

<div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel" style="margin-top: 20px;">
    <!-- Indicators -->
    <ol class="carousel-indicators">
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="2"></li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Wrapper for slides -->
    <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="item active">
            <img src="~/Content/media/images/mcc_bglr.png" style="width:100%; height: 500px;">
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <img src="~/Content/media/images/block3.jpg" style="width:100%; height: 500px;">
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <img src="~/Content/media/images/block5.jpg" style="width:100%; height: 500px;">
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Left and right controls -->
    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="prev">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
    </a>
    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="next">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
    </a>
</div>

@*<div id="splash"></div>*@

<div id="content">
    <div class="post">
        <h2 style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: xx-large; color: #FF9900; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 20px;">
             About Mount Carmel College
        </h2>
        <div class="entry">
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                <b><i>Mount Carmel College</i></b> is an educational institution primarily for women. Located in the garden city of Bangalore, the college reflects the dynamism and energy of this fast growing Indian metropolis through its exciting courses and innovative methods of teaching. The college is Re-Accredited with an A+ Grade(4th Cycle) by NAAC . A College with Potential for Excellence by UGC , Star College Status by DBT , Scientific and Industrial Research Organization(SIRO) by the Department of Scientific and Industrial Research(DSIR),Government of India . The college is affiliated to Bengaluru Central University but functions as an autonomous institution.Mount Carmel has always been the forerunner of constructive changes in academics to help generations enrich knowledge and enhance skills to match the pace of the world.
            </p>

            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;">
                Our Vision
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                <b><i>Mount Carmel College</i></b>, Bangalore, envisions a life-oriented education that
                    empowers the students through a humanizing and liberating process, to be agents of transformation and development at different levels of life. Enabled and empowered, they respond pro-actively to concerns and conflicts inherent in today’s reality, especially those of women and persons who are unable to exercise their freedom to be human, and work for the integrity of creation. The thrust is in the light of a ‘Civilization of Love’ - the Kingdom of God, as  envisaged and promoted by the Foundress, Mother Teresa of St. Rose of Lima.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; ">
                    Our Mission
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal;">
                ➢ To contribute to the transformation of society through being socially concious and responsible.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal;">
                ➢ To synergise women and the less privileged regarding their basic human rights.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal;">
                ➢ To promote inter-cultural and inter-religious and concern for the human family.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal;">
                ➢ To ficilitate leadership among the students enabling them to proactively involve themselves in social liberation.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal;">
                ➢ To work towards the integrity of creation and foster interconectedness, kinship and eco-justice.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal;">
                ➢ To provide quality, integral,vocational and career oriented education and create a climate for human and educational excellence.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="post">
        <div class="entry">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div style="clear: both;">&nbsp;</div>
</div>
